race.comment: CHAMPAGNE LANE (8) was heavily supported when facing the starter for the first time and didn't let backers down with a strong win over this track and trip. Has since been given time to further mature and can go back-to-back to start the career. BLITZWATER (7) was a strong Doomben winner before the break and looks to have plenty of upside. Gets some weight off from the low draw and can make her presence felt. THE SUN DANCE (1) has placed three of his past four and looks the be building up to another victory. Top-three credentials. OOHLALOUVRE (4) best of the rest while fresh. Has placed in each of her previous first up runs.
